{"type": "article", "id": 28928, "title": "海洋塑料制成的筷子", "description": "", "date": "2016-06-30T06:55:41Z", "super_tag": "", "tags": [], "category": 25, "column": 28, "author": 400262, "comment_count": 9, "praise_count": 43, "image": "img/article/article_show/20160703120244osYha03c7RBrIQ1v.jpg", "contents": "\n\n<p>          </p>\n<p>          </p>\n<p>根据今年初的一份<a href=\"https://www.theguardian.com/business/2016/jan/19/more-plastic-than-fish-in-the-sea-by-2050-warns-ellen-macarthur\">报道</a>，到 2050 年时海洋中的塑料将会比鱼还要多，阿姆斯特丹的设计师 Yavez S.E. Anthonio 将目光投向了这个亟待解决的环境污染问题，联合创意工作室 <a href=\"http://www.betterfuturefactory.com/\">Better Future Factory</a> 推出了 UmiHashi 塑料筷子。由于是将回收到的塑料融合在一起进行加工，每一双筷子都会呈现出独一无二的美丽颜色。目前塑料分类和筷子的制作都由团队手工进行，当筹集到足够资金之后就会用自动化机械取代。这是它的<a href=\"https://www.kickstarter.com/projects/anthonio/umi-hashi-chopsticks-made-of-ocean-plastic\">众筹链接</a>，售价为 20 欧元。</p>\n<div class=\"com-insert-images medium-insert-images-wide\">\n<figure class=\"\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160703120243dC0rh6lSvTOZ5pYx.jpg\" alt=\"\" class=\"\" data-ratio=\"1.21176471\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160703120243qso4lvLkzgBFPDYO.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.56323529\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure><figure style=\"margin:0;\">\r\n    <img src=\"img/uploads/20160703120244boAmKELC0JWliVp5.jpg\" alt=\"\" data-ratio=\"0.55964654\" data-format=\"jpeg\">\r\n</figure>\n</div>\n\n"}